<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March 10,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. White reports the passage, by large majority, of meat-inspection
                            bill in exceedingly severe form, and that the Government opposition
                            appeared not to be very earnest. The bill will now go to the Imperial
                            Council, where it will probably be somewhat modified.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>